title: JavaScript Assemble!
input:
add 10
subtract 2
multiply 3
subtract 4
add 9
multiply 10
add 989999
description: Make a function that receives a string containing commands (one per line) and applies them to a number (that starts as 0). The commands are add, subtract and mulltiply. So if you get the string "add 10\nsubtract 2\nmultiply 2" the result would be 8.
